chunk_text:
It follows then, that this knowledge exchange hopes to achieve the following: 
• To examine first-hand the factors and lessons learned from the Ministry of Tourism and Aviation of The Bahamas as a successful and longstanding example of sound tourism destination crisis management in the Caribbean; 
• To equip participants with knowledge to enhance existing tourism destination crisis management strategies; 
• To engage in knowledge exchange and networking with technical experts from state enterprises relative to tourism destination crisis management.
